\end{figure}

This study of statistical convergence also demonstrates an important feature of the present model: its mathematical simplifications permit a fast computer program to be used in order to simulate a large number of hops in an efficient manner. As an illustration, 10,000 hops can be simulated in about 1 minute (depending on the value of the shear velocity modelled) using a standard PC (i.e. Intel Core i3 3.10 GHz processor, 4 GB RAM). This feature is particularly important in the studies carried out in the following sections.\\
